1. Basic Java Questions
Write a program to print "Hello, World!".

Take two numbers as input and print their sum.

Check if an input number is even or odd.

Print the largest of three numbers entered by the user.

Find the factorial of a number using a loop.

Count vowels and consonants in a given string.

Swap values between two variables.

Write a program to reverse a string.

Check whether a given string is a palindrome.

Print numbers from 1 to 100 that are divisible by 5.

2. Intermediate Java Questions
Create a class Student with fields name, age, and grade. Take input and display the details.

Write a program to find the sum and average of numbers in an array.

Implement a simple calculator using switch-case.

Sort an array of integers in ascending order.

Find the second largest element in an array.

Create a method to check whether a number is prime.

Implement a menu-driven program to manage a contact list (add, search, delete).

Handle exceptions: Write a program to take input and catch NumberFormatException.

Create and read/write data to a file (text file).

Create and use an ArrayList to store and retrieve custom objects (like Book or Employee).

3. Advanced Java Questions
Implement a class hierarchy using inheritance (e.g., Animal â†’ Dog, Cat) with method overriding.

Use abstract classes and interfaces for a payment system simulation.

Design a banking system with Account, Savings, Current classes using OOP.

Implement encapsulation and demonstrate with getters/setters for private class members.

Write a program to serialize and deserialize an object.

Use HashMap to count the frequency of words in a given string.

Implement a program to remove duplicate elements from an array.

Simulate a simple hotel reservation system using classes, constructors, and methods.

Implement basic CRUD operations using file handling (add, display, update, delete records).

Write a generic method to swap elements in an array of any type.

